The special investigative unit will on Wednesday brief the Standing Committee on Public Accounts on SABC cases. JOHANNESBURG - The Special Investigative Unit will on Wednesday brief the Standing Committee on Public Accounts on their investigation into irregular tenders at the SABC. READ: SABC interim board hands SIU documents over controversial tender The SIU investigation into the state broadcaster found wrongdoing by the organization’s previous interim board on a security tender of R185-million given to Mafoko Security, despite Mjayeli Security and Technical Services reportedly scoring higher during the bidding process.